Class InvalidNumber

    public class InvalidNumber
extends java.lang.Exception

    Invalid Number

    The Invalid Number class adds the exception, "InvalidNumber". This exception was made for the NonStandard Integer Class(nsint). It is thrown when the base is less than 1, higher than 10, or if a digit is higher than the base allows.
    Since:
    2016-11-13
    Version:
    1.1
    Author:
    Minenash
    See Also:
